If Function is Differentiable we can find the Slope / gradeint but HOW? Using Backpropagation Algorithm.

## CHAIN RULE:

In model , there are chain of tensors functions/ operations , that are deruved using chain rule.

y = fg(x) = f(g(x))

i,e is grad(y,x) = grad(y, x1) * grad (x1,x)

This the Chain rule.
That is forward pass -> w,b -> l1 -> l2 -> loss
backward pass -> loss -> l2 -> l1 -> w,b

that is , from loss we can traverse back through and find each derivatives to ou the W,b

dloss/dw =  dloss        dl2         dl1
            ------  *  ---------- * -------
              dl2          dl1        dw

Same like for b , this the crust of chain rule , So with Chain rule and with Backpropagation algorithm we are calculating gradients with 
respect to the Any tensor.
